===Noun phrase===
'''[[ectopic]] [[pregnancy]]'''
#A [[pregnancy]] in which the [[fertilize]]d [[ovum]] is implanted in any tissue other than the [[uterus|uterine]] wall. Most ectopic pregnancies occur in the [[Fallopian tube]] (so-called [[tubal pregnancies]]), but implantation can also occur in the [[cervix]], [[ovary|ovaries]], and [[abdomen]]. An [[abdominal pregnancy]] or [[heterotopic pregnancy]] is rare, but a few, fabulously rare (about 1:60,000,000) cases are documented as coming to [[term]]; in the other instances, the mother dies first; an abdominal pregnancy is the supreme obstetrical emergency. All are treated by surgery where the life of the non-viable [[fetus]] is sacrificed for that of the mother.

